lliurex-auto-upgrade (0.3) focal; urgency=medium

  * making sure service doesn't wait an hour if it fails the very first time 
  * apt_cache.fix_broken() somehow unmarks packages to upgrade. Manually
    calling apt install -f for now to test the waters.
  * Since 0.2.3 is not able to upgrade packages and we want
    lliurex-auto-upgrade to be updated, lliurex-auto-upgrade-fix package was
    created to force the intallation of lliurex-auto-upgrade=0.3

